# Files to ignore when syncing from google/go-jsonnet (Go test suite).
# One .jsonnet filename per line. Lines starting with '#' are comments.
# Corresponding .golden files are also automatically ignored.
#
# Listed files have known behavioral differences between sjsonnet and go-jsonnet.
# Their golden files are generated by sjsonnet's refresh_golden_outputs.sh instead.

# --- Path-dependent tests ---
# std.thisFile returns filename-only in sjsonnet's test harness (working directory
# is the test suite dir), but a full relative path in go-jsonnet's test harness.
std.thisFile
std.thisFile2
stdlib_smoke_test

# --- Float rendering differences ---
# sjsonnet uses shortest round-trip representation (e.g. 1.42), while go-jsonnet
# emits more digits (e.g. 1.4199999999999999). sjsonnet's rendering is correct:
# the value round-trips to the same IEEE 754 double. jrsonnet agrees with sjsonnet.
builtin_escapeStringJson
builtin_manifestTomlEx
pow6
